{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/2020-01-03-welcome-to-nz-cellar-door/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"9aa3a946-818c-500e-9e6f-a9a3eff418d8","html":"<p>Over the coming months we will feature some of the best wineries in NZ for you to visit.  Make a day of it and build your own itinerary of cellar doors to visit, have a coffee or lunch, even stay for dinner and sample some of this countries great wines.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 400px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/news/static/0a2cdd8569ecb64173730b5dbeaaddcd/28275/marlborough.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 67%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"NZ Cellar Door\"\n        title=\"NZ Cellar Door\"\n        src=\"/news/static/0a2cdd8569ecb64173730b5dbeaaddcd/28275/marlborough.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/news/static/0a2cdd8569ecb64173730b5dbeaaddcd/28275/marlborough.jpg 400w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>If you are a cellar door, vineyard or a winery, you can <a href=\"/news/pricing\">list your wineries here</a>.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"January 03, 2020","title":"Welcome to NZ Cellar Door","description":"What is NZ Cellar Door?  A way to discover NZ wineries & vineyards that have cellar doors open to the public.  Cellar doors & tasting rooms are often located at or near the winery or a vineyard, but others are in a local restaurant, share spaces with other wine producers, Cellar doors are commonly located at or near the winery or a vineyard, but others are located in a local restaurant, share a space with other wine producers or retailers.\n\nNZ has some wonderful tasting rooms that offer food, entertainment, events, weddings, wine tasting and winery tours & trails. ","tags":["NZ Cellar Door","cellar doors","wineries","vineyards","New Zealand","wine tasting"]}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"id":"9aa3a946-818c-500e-9e6f-a9a3eff418d8"}}}